         All the stupid races have some sort of "god" that created them. Iksar/Erudite worship Cazic Thule. Gnomes worship Bertoxulous. Dark elves worship Innoruuk and humans are pretty much open to anything. Humans can be any class but Shaman and Beastlord (not sure on that...). They can worship any god their class they chose is available in as another race. All other races are suppose to follow one specific god that made them. Humans are open to any religion, kinda like RL. Not sure who made Hummies but they were made by somebody=p. </P><P>Far as a rate scale goes for gameplay. Iksar&gt;Dark Elf&gt;Erudite&gt;Gnome&gt;Human. Roleplay?... I have no frickin' clue=).</P><P>Good idea. Warrior is the best way to go. Boring but it helps you get going with the game=). Sometimes they are fun, never played one lol.</P><P>Warlock<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=250690" target="_blank">MY SHIT</a><BR><a href="http://www.vicious-arrogance.com/AO/Pics/Band/Dani/danicorpse.jpg" target="_blank">Ack!</a><BR><a href="http://www.vicious-arrogance.com/AO/Pics/PanDaemonAeon/42.jpg" target="_blank">It's me.</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
