        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=48253&amp;TOPIC_ID=5882&amp;FORUM_ID=13&amp;CAT_ID=2&amp;Forum_Title=Newbie+Land&amp;Topic_Title=Newbie+needs+help+to+choose+race&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Newbie armor quests?  Why hasn't anyone told me?  I have a lvl 11 gnome necro (she's so cute) and I didn't find any armor quests.  But maybe I should have looked harder.  ANYWAY, I'm nothing but pleased with my decision to start up a gnomish necro.  And I must say that I started her for the same reason that Smyrt did.  There aren't many gnomes that wander the lands of Norath, let alone gnomish necromancers.</P><P>As for my reasoning in not chosing the other classes...  Well, everyone and their mom has a DE necro.  And I really hate having severe KOS issues.  (I deal with that enough for my poor Iksar monk)  I had actually debated on weither or not to choose Erudite or Gnome.  Erudite appealed to me for the high starting INT, but then I remembered how great the areas in Erud are for socializing.  And everyone can tell you that NOBODY goes to Erud to hang out and have a good time.  It's kinda like my home town, nice place to live.  But it SUCKS if you wanna do anything.  Gotta jump the boat for anything worthwhile.</P><P>So that's why I chose to be Gnome.  True we have a slightly lower starting INT, but equip, experiense, and common sense can more than make up for it.  But that's all just my opinion.  I'm sure there's a reason that everyone plays DE necro's.</P><P>But yah, Human's SUCK.  Unless you're just learning the game in which case yah go human.  But once you learn the game, strip the character start something better and "twink" the new guy out.  Trust me, you'll have more fun that way.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
